How do you reduce AWS costs without compromising performance?

"I reduce AWS costs by right-sizing resources, using Reserved Instances for steady workloads, Spot for non-prod, Auto Scaling to avoid idle capacity, S3 lifecycle policies for storage, and scheduling dev environments to stop after hours — all without impacting production performance!" ✅
---
Right-Sizing EC2 Instances

Problem:
  Team provisioned t3.xlarge
  actual CPU usage only 15%
  paying for unused capacity ❌

Solution:
  CloudWatch → check CPU/memory metrics
  downsize to t3.medium
  same performance
  50% cost reduction ✅

Tools:
  AWS Compute Optimizer → recommends right size
  CloudWatch metrics    → actual usage data
---------
Reserved Instances / Savings Plans

On-Demand pricing:
  pay full price
  no commitment
  expensive for steady workloads ❌

Reserved Instances (1-3 year):
  up to 72% discount ✅
  good for production workloads
  predictable usage

Savings Plans:
  up to 66% discount ✅
  more flexible than RI
  applies across instance types

Spot Instances:
  up to 90% discount ✅
  good for:
    batch jobs
    CI/CD pipelines
    dev/test environments
  not for production ⚠️

